  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this randomized study was to assess the effectiveness of endomyocardial botulinum
      toxin injection for preventing post-procedural atrial fibrillation in patients undergoing the
      radiofrequency ablation of atrial flutter.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
